        <p>
          Humans can accelerate and decalerate as 3 m/s each second.
          Turning options are in parts of a full circle (centered around
          the direction of travel).  E.g. at 3 m/s this means 60&#176;
          off the direction of travel on either side per second.  For the
          sake of playability variance in this should be suppressed,
          although a 20% spread (for a 10 level difference) with Agility
          modification could be appropriate.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fatigue is acrued at the 10 points per minute (or 1 per second)
          for the generated maximum sprint speed. Fractions (which cannot
          exceed 1) of that speed generate the corresponding fractional
          fatigue rate. E.g. running at half the maximum speed gives 5 points
          per minute (or 1 per 12 seconds).  Only simple fractions are allowed.
        </p>
