        <p>
          The listed weight can be lifted without dedicated tools.  At that point
          any activity is at -10.  This scales linearly down or up.  That means that
          any fraction of the weight carried also incurs the same fraction of
          -10 as penalty. Any multiple carried also gives the corresponding multiple
          as penalty.  Note that with certain penalties usually trivial activities
          (i.e. no roll required) become difficult, for instance not stumbling. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Still without tools, activity with both hands is impossible. Freeing one 
          hand incurs twice the penalty and assumes that the weight is liftable that
          way.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fatigue is acrued at the 10 points per minute (or 1 per second)
          for the generated maximum lift. Fractions (which cannot exceed 1) of
          that lift generate the corresponding fractional
          fatigue rate. E.g. lifting half the maximum weight gives 5 points
