        <h1 id="combat">Combat</h1>
        <p>
          The following table is rolled for each combatant, adding any
          bonuses and subtracting any penalties.  The time is the number
          of seconds, which it takes to achieve the set <em>wound level</em>
          zero.  The <em>wound level</em> can be set higher, but then this
          number is subtracted. Estimated time and level can be played out
          against each other.  The intended <em>wound level</em> must be
          declared before the roll and in multiples of 5.  Once a (rolled)
          progression has reached its goal, a new skill roll is necessary.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any effects from wounds or other external influences in combat are
          applied immediately to pending progressions.  At the actors choice
          it can offset the goal or the time.  To prevent players from immediately
          aborting "bad" rolls, mandatory secret rolls by the GM can be used.
        </p>
        <p>
          If so desired, the intended wound level can be randomized in the usual
          way.  This can not be modified except through <em>control</em>.
          Alternatively, if time is fixed, a best effort attack can be made. For
          instance, if an opponent was downed and will get up within a few seconds
          and the bonus shall be used for better or worse.  In that case always
          spread the actual wound level around the least favorable time for the
          attacker.
