        <h3 id="com-2">Page 2-5</h3>
        <p>
          <em>Endurance</em> equals <em>Stamina</em>.  <em>Move</em> is a
          velocity as given above.  <em>Dodge</em> is added to <em>Defense</em>
          through Row-5-Addition. On the <em>Weapon Data</em> the Skill, WQ, 
          and OML are ignored. A/D and HM are divided by 5.  Custom weapon
          are descriptive only.
        </p>
        <p>
          Armour is used as is, except the <em>Protection and Encumbrance</em> 
          part, wich is only descriptive. The bonus to an attack is a bonus of
          attacker's choice between all the relevant B/E/P values of his weapon.
          After the goal is reached, the corresponding defender B/E/P is deducted
          from the wound level.
        </p>
